<TITLE> Khaleda set to address Paltan gathering </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 2 (bdnews24.com)  Opposition leader Khaleda Zia is set to address Saturday afternoon a public rally organised by the Bangladesh Nationalist Party's labour wing Jatiyatabadi Sramik Dal at Paltan ground in the capital. BNP asked the Dhaka Metropolitan Police Friday to ensure "enough security" for the planned public meeting marking the May Day, party officials said. Sramik Dal's president and BNP' joint secretary general Nazrul Islam Khan told bdnews24.com Saturday morning the meeting will start at 3pm. "Khaleda will make an important speech there," he said. Prime minister Sheikh Hasina addressed a huge rally organised by ruling Awami League's labour front Jatiya Sramik League at the same venue Friday. This will be the first meeting of the BNP at Paltan since its massive defeat in the Dec 29, 2008 parliamentary elections. Khaleda last delivered speech at Paltan on Dec 27, the last day of election campaigns. Metropolitan BNP's former president Sadeque Hossain Khoka said supporters of BNP's all fronts will attend the meeting. "Since it is our first rally in the capital after the election, we have taken massive preparation," Khoka, also Dhaka mayor, added. b
